abstract: Jimmy Kimmel joked that President Trump should be asking the turkeys Bread and Butter for a pardon, “not the other way around.”

abstract: The president took on the impeachment inquiry, Democrats and the news media in his first return to the state as a formal resident.
snippet: The president took on the impeachment inquiry, Democrats and the news media in his first return to the state as a formal resident.
lead_paragraph: SUNRISE, Fla. — President Trump on Tuesday raged against the Democrats’ impeachment inquiry, lobbed attacks at his adversaries in the Washington establishment and angrily defended his health during an unfettered, raucous rally that marked his return to Florida as a formal resident.

abstract: The president’s lawyer met with the head of the department’s criminal division about a money laundering case involving Alejandro Betancourt López.
snippet: The president’s lawyer met with the head of the department’s criminal division about a money laundering case involving Alejandro Betancourt López.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Rudolph W. Giuliani, President Trump’s personal lawyer, represented a wealthy Venezuelan businessman in a discussion with the Justice Department about heading off charges against the businessman in a money laundering and bribery case.

abstract: The comments, made in an interview with the former Fox News host Bill O’Reilly, came three weeks after nine American citizens, including six children, were killed in Mexico.
snippet: The comments, made in an interview with the former Fox News host Bill O’Reilly, came three weeks after nine American citizens, including six children, were killed in Mexico.
lead_paragraph: President Trump said in an interview posted online Tuesday that he planned to designate Mexican drug cartels as terrorist organizations, owing to what he said was the high number of Americans killed by their activities.

abstract: White House lawyers briefed President Trump in late August about the complaint, people familiar with the matter said.
snippet: White House lawyers briefed President Trump in late August about the complaint, people familiar with the matter said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump had already been briefed on a whistle-blower’s complaint about his dealings with Ukraine when he unfroze military aid for the country in September, according to two people familiar with the matter.
